id: hac-0zez
title: Wizard read-only option collides with global boolean flag
description: Full-program non-interactive setup rejects the wizard value because its --read-only <boolean> option conflicts with the root --read-only boolean.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[5]: cli,commander,regression,settings,wizard
created_at: "2026-07-22T04:54:29.842Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-22T04:58:01.313Z"
deadline: "2026-07-23T04:54:29.842Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-22T04:58:01.312Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 45
acceptance_criteria: Non-interactive full-program wizard saves read-only true and validates the live connection
definition_of_ready: Failure reproduced through installed hassio binary
goal: best-agent-home-assistant-cli
objective: reliable-setup-wizard
value: Agents and CI can provision safety settings non-interactively
impact: Restores production setup workflow
outcome: Unambiguous --config-read-only option with regression and live proof
why_now: Live acceptance testing exposed the production-only collision
parent: hac-km4t
reviewer: unbraind
risk: medium
confidence: 100
sprint: websocket-contracts
release: 2026.7.22
severity: high
environment: Installed hassio root program with Commander 15
repro_steps: Run hassio settings wizard --non-interactive with --read-only true
resolution: Renamed the saved wizard setting to --config-read-only while preserving global --read-only invocation semantics.
expected_result: Non-interactive full-program wizard saves readOnly=true.
actual_result: Installed wizard saved isolated settings/auth/data with auth mode 0600; validate and doctor passed live.
affected_version: 2026.7.21-2
fixed_version: 2026.7.22
component: settings-wizard
regression: false
customer_impact: Non-interactive safety configuration fails
