comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-22T04:54:29.842Z",codex-root,Renamed the saved setting option; global --read-only retains per-invocation semantics.
  "2026-07-22T04:54:50.068Z",codex-root,Installed full-program acceptance test reproduced the inherited-option collision; --config-read-only now saves the intended setting while root --read-only remains invocation-only.
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-22T04:54:29.842Z",codex-root,Full root-program validation is required for inherited Commander option collisions.
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-22T04:54:29.842Z",codex-root,Subcommand-only tests cannot detect root and child option-name ambiguity.
  "2026-07-22T04:54:50.767Z",codex-root,Production Commander trees must be tested as a whole when global and child options can overlap.
